title: Kyung Wha Chung - Chicago Sym. Orch. - Berg - Bartok Violin Conc
description:
Ok... Hi again folks. Here we have two excellent viloin concertos, one by Alban Berg and the other by Bela Bartok. Superbly played by Kyung Wha Chung accompanied by the Chicago Symphony Orchestra conducted by Sir Georg Solti. This one is a simply pure pleasure. Alright, in summary, this is not Kwai Chang Caine, he was fictional; this Kyung Wha Chung (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyung-wha_Chung), as she's the real-deal. WEnjoy... 

Kyung Wha Chung / Chicago Symphony Orchestra, Sir Georg Solti
Alban Berg / Bela Bartok - Violin Concertos
London Records
411 804-2
1984


Tracklist:

Berg: Violin Concerto
01 Violin Concerto: I. Andante

Bartok: Violin Concerto No. 1, Op. Posth.
05 Violin Concerto No. 1, Op. Posth.: I. Andante sostenuto
06 Violin Concerto No. 1, Op. Posth.: II. Allegro giocoso


Complete full HQ scans of this CD release included


Hope you enjoy the music... and until next time
